title: Navy SEALs missing at sea after ship-boarding mission off Somalia
description: Two members of the elite Navy SEALs went missing Thursday after attempting to board a ship in the Gulf of Aden off the coast of Somalia.

title: Frederik X: A visual biography of Denmark’s next king
description: A look at his life, from ‘party prince’ to monarch.

title: Queen Margrethe II: A visual biography of Denmark’s abdicating monarch
description: Denmark’s Queen Margrethe II steps down this weekend as Europe’s longest-serving monarch and the first Danish royal to abdicate since 1146.

title: Taiwan elects Lai Ching-te as president. China calls it a dangerous choice.
description: Lai Ching-te of the Democratic Progressive Party has been elected president of Taiwan, an outcome that will anger China, which views him as a separatist.

title: How drug traffickers made the Galápagos Islands their gas station
description: The beloved UNESCO World Heritage site is being pulled into the booming cocaine trade that’s fueling Ecuador’s violence.

title: In D.C., thousands expected to attend March for Gaza rally on Saturday
description: Thousands of protesters are expected at a rally and march in downtown D.C. on Saturday calling for a cease-fire in Gaza and a halt to U.S. aid to Israel.

title: In photos: Taiwan votes in presidential election
description: Voters headed to the polls Saturday as three candidates vie for the presidency in a contentious election that could transform Taiwan’s relationship with China.

title: Israel-Gaza war live updates: New U.S. strike on Houthi site follows sprawling attacks
description: The strike early Saturday comes after a U.S.- and U.K.-led coalition launched a wave of attacks on Houthi militants in Yemen, and as Houthis vow retaliation.

title: Belgorod, in western Russia, hit hard as Ukraine retaliates for airstrikes
description: Most of Russia is insulated from the war, but a Ukrainian strike killed 25 people in Belgorod on Dec. 30, the largest civilian toll in Russia since its February 2022 invasion of Ukraine.

title: In Yemen’s Houthis, U.S. and Britain face a ready, war-tested foe
description: Analysts say the assault has played directly into the hands of a battle-tested militant group whose standing in the region has only been enhanced.
